#. Tag: title
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:9
#, no-c-format
msgid "Setting Up a Virtual Machine Host"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:15
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This section documents how to set up and use &productname; &productnumber; "
"as a virtual machine host."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:19
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Usually, the hardware requirements for the &dom0; are the same as those for "
"the &productname; operating system, but additional CPU, disk, memory, and "
"network resources should be added to accommodate the resource demands of all "
"planned &vmguest; systems."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:26
#, no-c-format
msgid "Resources"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:27
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Remember that &vmguest; systems, like physical machines, perform better when "
"they run on faster processors and have access to more system memory."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:37
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The virtual machine host requires several software packages and their "
"dependencies to be installed. To install all necessary packages, run &yast; "
"<guimenu>Software Management</guimenu>, select <menuchoice><guimenu>View</"
"guimenu> <guimenu>Patterns</guimenu></menuchoice> and choose <guimenu>&xen; "
"Virtual Machine Host Server</guimenu> for installation. The installation can "
"also be performed with &yast; using the module "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>Virtualization</guimenu><guimenu>Install Hypervisor and "
"Tools</guimenu></menuchoice>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:47
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"After the &xen; software is installed, restart the computer and, on the boot "
"screen, choose the newly added option with the &xen; kernel."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:51
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Updates are available through your update channel. To be sure to have the "
"latest updates installed, run &yast; <guimenu>Online Update</guimenu> after "
"the installation has finished."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:57
#, no-c-format
msgid "Best Practices and Suggestions"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:59
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When installing and configuring the &sle; operating system on the host, be "
"aware of the following best practices and suggestions:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:66
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If the host should always run as &xen; host, run &yast; <menuchoice> "
"<guimenu>System</guimenu> <guimenu>Boot Loader</guimenu> </menuchoice> and "
"activate the &xen; boot entry as default boot section."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:73
#, no-c-format
msgid "In &yast;, click <guimenu>System &gt; Boot Loader</guimenu>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:78
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Change the default boot to the <guimenu>&xen;</guimenu> label, then click "
"<guimenu>Set as Default</guimenu>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:84
#, no-c-format
msgid "Click <guimenu>Finish</guimenu>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:91
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For best performance, only the applications and processes required for "
"virtualization should be installed on the virtual machine host."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:97
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When using both iSCSI and OCFS2 to host &xen; images, the latency required "
"for OCFS2 default timeouts in &sls; 12 may not be met. To reconfigure this "
"timeout, run <command>systemctl configure o2cb</command> or edit "
"<literal>O2CB_HEARTBEAT_THRESHOLD</literal> in the system configuration."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:105
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you intend to use a watchdog device attached to the &xen; host, use only "
"one at a time. It is recommended to use a driver with actual hardware "
"integration over a generic software one."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:115
#, no-c-format
msgid "Hardware Monitoring"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:116
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The &dom0; Kernel is running virtualized, so tools like <command>irqbalance</"
"command> or <command>lscpu</command> will not reflect the real hardware "
"characteristics."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:124
#, no-c-format
msgid "Managing &dom0; Memory"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:126
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When the host is set up, a percentage of system memory is reserved for the "
"hypervisor, and all remaining memory is automatically allocated to &dom0;."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:131
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A better solution is to set a default amount of memory for &dom0;, so the "
"memory can be allocated appropriately to the hypervisor. An adequate amount "
"would be 20 percent of the total system memory up to 4 GiB. A recommended "
"minimum amount would be 512 MiB"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:139
#, no-c-format
msgid "Minimum amount of Memory"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:140
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The minimum amount of memory heavily depends on how many &vmguest;(s) the "
"host should handle. So be sure you have enough memory to support all your "
"&vmguest;s. If the value is too low, the host system may hang when multiple "
"&vmguest;s use most of the memory."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:149
#, no-c-format
msgid "Setting a Maximum Amount of Memory"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:152
#, no-c-format
msgid "Determine the amount of memory to set for &dom0;."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:157
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"At &dom0;, type <command>xl info</command> to view the amount of memory that "
"is available on the machine. The memory that is currently allocated by "
"&dom0; can be determined with the command <command>xl list</command>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:164
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Run <menuchoice> <guimenu>&yast;</guimenu> <guimenu>Boot Loader</guimenu> </"
"menuchoice>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:170
#, no-c-format
msgid "Select the &xen; section."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:175
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In <guimenu>Additional &xen; Hypervisor Parameters</guimenu>, add "
"<command>dom0_mem=<replaceable>mem_amount</replaceable></command> where "
"<replaceable>mem_amount</replaceable> is the maximum amount of memory to "
"allocate to &dom0;. Add <command>K</command>, <command>M</command>, or "
"<command>G</command>, to specify the size, for example, "
"<command>dom0_mem=768M</command>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:185
#, no-c-format
msgid "Restart the computer to apply the changes."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:191
#, no-c-format
msgid "&xen; &dom0; Memory"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:192
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When using the XL tool stack and the <command>dom0_mem=</command> option for "
"the &xen; hypervisor in &grub; you need to disable xl <emphasis>autoballoon</"
"emphasis> in <filename>etc/xen/xl.conf</filename>, otherwise launching VMs "
"will fail with errors about not being able to balloon down &dom0;. So add "
"<emphasis>autoballoon=0</emphasis> to <filename>xl.conf</filename> if you "
"have the <command>dom0_mem=</command> option specified for &xen;. Also see "
"<link xlink:href=\"http://wiki.xen.org/wiki/"
"Xen_Best_Practices#Xen_dom0_dedicated_memory_and_preventing_dom0_memory_ballooning"
"\">Xen dom0 memory</link>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:207
#, no-c-format
msgid "Network Card in Fully Virtualized Guests"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:209
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In a fully virtualized guest, the default network card is an emulated "
"Realtek network card. However, it also possible to use the split network "
"driver to run the communication between &dom0; and a &vmguest;. By default, "
"both interfaces are presented to the &vmguest;, because the drivers of some "
"operating systems require both to be present."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:217
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When using &sle;, only the paravirtualized network cards are available for "
"the &vmguest; by default. The following network options are available:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:224
#, no-c-format
msgid "emulated"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:226
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To use an emulated network interface like an emulated Realtek card, specify "
"<literal>type=ioemu</literal> in the <literal>vif</literal> device section "
"of the domain xl configuration. An example configuration would look like:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:232
#, no-c-format
msgid "vif = [ 'type=ioemu,mac=00:16:3e:5f:48:e4,bridge=br0' ]"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:233
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Find more details about the xl configuration in the <filename>xl.conf</"
"filename> manual page <command>man 5 xl.conf</command>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:241
#, no-c-format
msgid "paravirtualized"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:243
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When you specify <literal>type=vif</literal> and do not specify a model or "
"type, the paravirtualized network interface is used:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:247
#, no-c-format
msgid "vif = [ 'type=vif,mac=00:16:3e:5f:48:e4,bridge=br0,backen=0' ]"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:251
#, no-c-format
msgid "emulated and paravirtualized"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:253
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If the administrator should be offered both options, simply specify both "
"type and model. The xl configuration would look like:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:257
#, no-c-format
msgid "vif = [ 'type=ioemu,mac=00:16:3e:5f:48:e4,model=rtl8139,bridge=br0' ]"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:258
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In this case, one of the network interfaces should be disabled on the "
"&vmguest;."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:267
#, no-c-format
msgid "Starting the Virtual Machine Host"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:269
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If virtualization software is correctly installed, the computer boots to "
"display the &grub; boot loader with a <guimenu>&xen;</guimenu> option on the "
"menu. Select this option to start the virtual machine host."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:276
#, no-c-format
msgid "Xen and Kdump"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:277
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In &xen;, the hypervisor manages the memory resource. If you need to reserve "
"system memory for a recovery kernel in &dom0;, this memory need to be "
"reserved by the hypervisor. Thus, it is necessary to add the parameter "
"<systemitem>crashkernel=size</systemitem> to the <literal>kernel</literal> "
"line instead of using the line with the other boot options."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:284
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For more information on the crashkernel parameter, see <xref linkend=\"sec."
"tuning.kexec.crashkernel\"/>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:290
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If the <guimenu>&xen;</guimenu> option is not on the &grub; menu, review the "
"steps for installation and verify that the &grub; boot loader has been "
"updated. If the installation has been done without selecting the &xen; "
"pattern, run the &yast; <guimenu>Software Management</guimenu>, select the "
"filter <guimenu>Patterns</guimenu> and choose <guimenu>&xen; Virtual Machine "
"Host Server</guimenu> for installation."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:299
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"After booting the hypervisor, the &dom0; virtual machine starts and displays "
"its graphical desktop environment. If you did not install a graphical "
"desktop, the command line environment appears."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:306
#, no-c-format
msgid "Graphics Problems"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:307
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Sometimes it may happen that the graphics system does not work properly. In "
"this case, add <literal>vga=ask</literal> to the boot parameters. To "
"activate permanent settings, use <literal>vga=mode-0x???</literal> where "
"<literal>???</literal> is calculated as <literal>0x100</literal> + VESA mode "
"from <link xlink:href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/VESA_BIOS_Extensions"
"\"></link>, for example <literal>vga=mode-0x361</literal>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:318
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Before starting to install virtual guests, make sure that the system time is "
"correct. To do this, configure NTP (Network Time Protocol) on the "
"controlling domain:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:326
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In &yast; select <menuchoice> <guimenu>Network Services</guimenu> "
"<guimenu>NTP Configuration</guimenu> </menuchoice>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:332
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Select the option to automatically start the NTP daemon during boot. Provide "
"the IP address of an existing NTP time server, then click <guimenu>Finish</"
"guimenu>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:341
#, no-c-format
msgid "Time Services on Virtual Guests"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:342
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Hardware clocks commonly are not very precise. All modern operating systems "
"try to correct the system time compared to the hardware time by means of an "
"additional time source. To get the correct time on all &vmguest; systems, "
"also activate the network time services on each respective guest or make "
"sure that the guest uses the system time of the host. For more about "
"<literal>Independent Wallclocks</literal> in &productname; see <xref linkend="
"\"sec.xen.guests.suse.time\"/>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:353
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For more information about managing virtual machines, see <xref linkend="
"\"cha.xen.manage\"/>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:359
#, no-c-format
msgid "&pciback;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:361
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To take full advantage of &vmguest; systems, it is sometimes necessary to "
"assign specific PCI devices to a dedicated domain. When using fully "
"virtualized guests, this functionality is only available if the chipset of "
"the system supports this feature, and if it is activated from the BIOS."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:368
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This feature is available from both AMD* and Intel*. For AMD machines, the "
"feature is called <xref linkend=\"gloss.vt.acronym.iommu\"/>; in Intel "
"speak, this is <xref linkend=\"gloss.vt.acronym.vtd\"/>. Note that Intel-VT "
"technology is not sufficient to use this feature for fully virtualized "
"guests. To make sure that your computer supports this feature, ask your "
"supplier specifically to deliver a system that supports &pciback;."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:378 xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:529
#, no-c-format
msgid "Limitations"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:380
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Some graphics drivers use highly optimized ways to access DMA. This is not "
"supported, and thus using graphics cards may be difficult."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:386
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When accessing PCI devices behind a <xref linkend=\"gloss.vt.acronym.pcie\"/"
"> bridge, all of the PCI devices must be assigned to a single guest. This "
"limitation does not apply to <xref linkend=\"gloss.vt.acronym.pcie\"/> "
"devices."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:394
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Guests with dedicated PCI devices cannot be migrated live to a different "
"host."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:401
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The configuration of &pciback; is twofold. First, the hypervisor must be "
"informed at boot time that a PCI device should be available for reassigning. "
"Second, the PCI device must be assigned to the &vmguest;."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:408
#, no-c-format
msgid "Configuring the Hypervisor for &pciback;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:411
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Select a device to reassign to a &vmguest;. To do this, run <command>lspci</"
"command> and read the device number. For example, if <command>lspci</"
"command> contains the following line:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:416
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"06:01.0 Ethernet controller: Digital Equipment Corporation DECchip 21142/43 "
"(rev 41)"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:417
#, no-c-format
msgid "In this case, the PCI number is <literal>(06:01.0)</literal>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:422
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Run <menuchoice><guimenu>&yast;</guimenu><guimenu>System</guimenu> "
"<guimenu>Boot Loader</guimenu></menuchoice>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:428
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Select the <literal>&xen;</literal> section and press <guimenu>Edit</"
"guimenu>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:434
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Add the PCI number to the <guimenu>Optional Kernel Command Line Parameter</"
"guimenu> line:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:438
#, no-c-format
msgid "pciback.hide=(06:01.0)"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:441
#, no-c-format
msgid "Press <guimenu>OK</guimenu> and exit &yast;."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:446
#, no-c-format
msgid "Reboot the system."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:451
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Check if the device is in the list of assignable devices with the command"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:454
#, no-c-format
msgid "xl pci-assignable-list"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:458
#, no-c-format
msgid "Dynamic Assignment with xl"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:459
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To avoid restarting the host system, you can use dynamic assignment with xl "
"to use &pciback;."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:463
#, no-c-format
msgid "Begin by making sure that dom0 has the pciback module loaded:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:466
#, no-c-format
msgid "modprobe pciback"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:467
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Then make a device assignable by using <command>xl pci-assignable-add</"
"command>. For example, to make the device <emphasis>06:01.0</emphasis> "
"available for guests, run the command:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:472
#, no-c-format
msgid "xl pci-assignable-add 06:01.0"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:477
#, no-c-format
msgid "Assigning PCI Devices to &vmguest; Systems"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:478
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"There are several possibilities to dedicate a PCI device to a &vmguest;:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:483
#, no-c-format
msgid "Adding the device while installing:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:485
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"During installation, add the <literal>pci</literal> line to the "
"configuration file:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:489
#, no-c-format
msgid "pci=['06:01.0']"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:493
#, no-c-format
msgid "Hotplugging PCI devices to &vmguest; systems"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:495
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The command <literal>xl</literal> can be used to add or remove PCI devices "
"on the fly. To add the device with number <literal>06:01.0</literal> to a "
"guest with name <literal>sles12</literal> use:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:501
#, no-c-format
msgid "xl pci-attach sles12 06:01.0"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:505
#, no-c-format
msgid "Adding the PCI device to Xend"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:507
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To add the device to the guest permanently, add the following snippet to the "
"guest configuration file:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:511
#, no-c-format
msgid "pci = [ '06:01.0,power_mgmt=1,permissive=1' ]"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:515
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"After assigning the PCI device to the &vmguest;, the guest system must care "
"for the configuration and device drivers for this device."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:522
#, no-c-format
msgid "&vgaback;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:523
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&xen; 4.0 and newer supports VGA graphics adapter pass-through on fully "
"virtualized &vmguest;s. The guest can take full control of the graphics "
"adapter with high-performance full 3D and video acceleration."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:531
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&vgaback; functionality is similar to &pciback; and as such also requires "
"<xref linkend=\"gloss.vt.acronym.iommu\"/> (or Intel VT-d) support from the "
"mainboard chipset and BIOS."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:538
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Only the primary graphics adapter (the one that is used when you power on "
"the computer) can be used with &vgaback;."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:544
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&vgaback; is supported only for fully virtualized guests. Paravirtual guests "
"(PV) are not supported."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:550
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The graphics card cannot be shared between multiple &vmguest;s using "
"&vgaback; &mdash; you can dedicate it to one guest only."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:556
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To enable &vgaback;, add the following settings to your fully virtualized "
"guest configuration file:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:560
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"gfx_passthru=1\n"
"pci=['yy:zz.n']"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:561
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"where <literal>yy:zz.n</literal> is the PCI controller ID of the VGA "
"graphics adapter as found with <command>lspci -v</command> on &dom0;."
msgstr ""

