#. Tag: title
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:633
#, no-c-format
msgid "USB Pass-Through with PVUSB"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:640
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"PVUSB is a new high performance method for USB Pass-Through from dom0 to the "
"virtualized guests. PVUSB supports both, USB 2.0 and USB 1.1 devices. PVUSB "
"uses a paravirtualized front- and back-end interface. With PVUSB, there are "
"two ways to add USB devices to a guest:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:650
#, no-c-format
msgid "via the config file at domain creation time"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:655
#, no-c-format
msgid "via hot-plug while the VM is running"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:662
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"PVUSB uses a paravirtualized front- and back-end interface. PVUSB supports "
"USB 1.1 and USB 2.0, and it works for both, PV and HVM guests. In order to "
"use PVUSB, you need usbfront in your guest OS, and usbback in dom0 or usb "
"backend in qemu. With &sls;, usb backend comes with qemu."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:683
#, no-c-format
msgid "Use <command>lsusb</command> to list the USB devices on the system:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:686
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.root;lsusb\n"
"Bus 001 Device 001: ID 1d6b:0002 Linux Foundation 2.0 root hub\n"
"Bus 002 Device 003: ID 0461:4d15 Primax Electronics, Ltd Dell Optical Mouse\n"
"Bus 002 Device 001: ID 1d6b:0001 Linux Foundation 1.1 root hub"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:687
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To pass through the Dell mouse, for instance, specify either 0461:4d15 or "
"2.3 (you must remove leading zeros, otherwise <command>xl</command> would "
"interpret the numbers as octal values)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:694
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"As of Xen 4.7, <command>xl</command> PVUSB support and hot-plug support is "
"introduced."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:698
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In the configuration file, specify USB controllers and USB host devices with "
"<literal>usbctrl</literal> and <literal>usbdev</literal>. For example, in "
"case of HVM guests:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:705
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"usbctrl=['type=qubs,version=2,ports=4', 'type=qubs,version=1,ports=4', ]\n"
"usbdev=['hostbus=2, hostaddr=1, controller=0,port=1', ]"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:713
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"It is important to specify <literal>type=qusb</literal> for the controller "
"of HVM guests."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:719
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To manage hot-pluggin PVUSB devices, use the <literal>usbctrl-attach</"
"literal>, <literal>usbctrl-detach</literal>, <literal>usb-list</literal>, "
"<literal>usbdev-attach</literal> and <literal>usb-detach</literal> "
"subcommands. For example:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:725
#, no-c-format
msgid "Create a USB controller which is version USB 1.1 and has 8 ports:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:728
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.root;xl usbctrl-attach test_vm version=1 ports=8 type=qusb"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:729
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Find the first available controller:port in the domain, and attach USB "
"device whose busnum:devnum is 2:3 to it; you can also specify "
"<literal>controller</literal> and <literal>port</literal>:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:735
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.root;xl usbdev-attach test_vm hostbus=2 hostaddr=3"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:737
#, no-c-format
msgid "Show all USB controllers and USB devices in the domain:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: xen_virtualization_vhost.xml:740
